{{Wireless embedded system |brand=TRENDnet |model=TEW-732BR |revision=V1.0R |upc=710931130089 |asin=B00E37JFH0 |fcc_date=02/27/2013 |manuf_country=China |is_manuf=No |manuf=Cameo |type=wireless router |fcc_id=XU8TEW732BR |pwr_v=5 |pwr_amp=1 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=Atheros |cpu1_model=AR1321 |cpu1_cspeed=535 |fla1=8 |fla1_brand=GigaDevice |fla1_model=25Q64BSIG |ram1=64 |ram1_brand=Nanya |ram1_model=NT5TU32M16DG-AC |jtag=14-pin header,, unpopulated |serial=4-pin header |wi1_chip1_brand=Atheros |wi1_chip1_model=AR1321 |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_ant_conn=U.FL |wi1_txchains=2 |wi1_rxchains=2 |wi1_sstreams=2 |eth_cpu=true |lan_speed=100M |lan_ports=4 |wan_ports=1 |tp_firmware=OpenWrt |802dot11_protocols=bgn |default_ssid=TRENDnet732-XXXX |default_ssid_regex=^TRENDnet732-[a-f0-9]4$ |default_ip=192.168.10.1 |default_user=admin |default_pass=admin |oui=D8:EB:97 |oui_eth=D8:EB:97 }} ''N300 Wireless Router'' This router sits upright like the [[ZyXEL NBG5715]]. "Rev:A0-2" and "Made In China" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. The WiSoC used is an AR1321-AL1A. Default settings are per the FCC manual. The '''XXXX''' in the default SSID pattern appears to be lower-case hex digits. :The FCC label, however, specifies the default SSID pattern as '''TRENDnet732XXXX'''. ''(The board contain a 4-pin UART (serial) output, as well as a 14-pin output (possibly for JTAG?).''
''Headers are unpopulated, need to be soldered. Board also has silkscreen and holes for one USB)''
